<p class = "strong text-justify" id = "1"> 1. General provisions. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.1. The virtual-rugby.com forum is a private resource, part of the Virtual Rugby League. By using it, you agree to be guided by these Rules. Violators of the Rules are punished with warnings and can be blocked temporarily or permanently. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.2. The forum is post-moderated, i.e. messages are added immediately, and they are "decimated" later. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.3. Forum moderators keep order on the forum. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.3.1. Moderators exercise control over the forums, can edit, delete posts, close and move threads / posts to the appropriate / more appropriate section of the forum. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.3.2. Discussion of the actions of the moderators and the Rules of using the forum is prohibited everywhere, except in the topics specially intended for this: Complaints about the actions of the forum moderators and the Forum Rules. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.3.3. Forum moderators need to write private messages, and not write them directly in the topic about completely different things. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.3.4. Forum moderators have the right to preferential interpretation of certain points of the Forum Rules in case of statements about the presence of a double meaning in such points on the part of the user. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.4. All messages reflect the opinions of their authors, and the Administration does not bear any responsibility for them. If you think that any messages are against the law, contain commercial secrets or are capable of causing harm to someone, you can report this to the forum moderators. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.5. Adhere to the established culture of communication on our forum. We create our own habitat. Let\'s be polite and friendly to each other! If you see violations or are provoked to do so by other forum members, do not be led by the violators. You can write a letter to the forum administrator indicating the violation. The rest is the responsibility of the moderator. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.6. If you are new here, do not flatter yourself with the tone of some of the discussions. Many people have known each other for a long time and can afford such a tone towards each other. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.7. If you made a mistake, for example, duplicated a message, accidentally sent a response to the wrong place, or sent an empty message, then leave it as it is. Readers will figure it out, the moderator will clean it up later. If you really want to draw his attention to this, send him a private message. You shouldn\'t write new messages and comment on your mistakes, and then write messages apologizing for such a flood. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.8. When choosing an avatar, make sure that there is no similar avatar on the forum, otherwise the author, who had this avatar before, has the right to ask the administrator to remove the duplicate from your profile. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 1.9. Recommendations for creating new themes: </p>
