<p class = "text-justify"> 2.3.5. Having little content (for example, "Help !!" or "Have a question") or a title that does not correspond to the content. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.3.6. With advertising of a player, team or tournament in all sections except the appropriate ones (Transfer / Rent / Registration and teams ...). Exceptions: It is allowed to write about players / teams in the national forums of the federation to which the player / team belongs. Note: It is allowed to create no more than one hot topic per team or tournament in any of the above sections. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> All topics, the creation of which is prohibited by the above rules, can be closed or deleted by moderators without warning. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4. It is forbidden to write messages containing: </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.1. Appeals to violate the rules of the game, forum and legislation. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.2. Knowingly false information, slander, unsupported information that may harm someone\'s  reputation. Dishonest methods of conducting discussions in the form of "distorting" the statements of the interlocutors, editing their own messages in order to distort their original meaning are prohibited. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.3. Heavy-tone messages, obscene expressions and insults in any form. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.4. "Assaults" on individuals, groups of individuals, threats of physical violence, etc. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.5. Baseless claims that "this" is better and "this" is worse. If there are facts - good (mention it is your experience or someone else\'s ). No - don\'t forget to add that this is your personal opinion. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.6. Pointless or low-content information that does not carry a semantic load (flood) - for example, messages consisting of only emoticons, "+1" and the like. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.7. Excessive amount of grammatical errors, slang words, modern network "dialects". They tell forum visitors about your disrespectful attitude towards them. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.8. More than half of CAPITAL LETTERS. Respect your interlocutors, they may think that you are yelling at them. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.9. Content that is completely remote from the topic (malicious offtopic). </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.10. A font with a size / color different from the default, unless you highlight a word or phrase if you want to emphasize their importance. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.11. Insulting fans of real teams in the form of various nicknames (such as "pigs", "horses", "homeless people", etc.), as well as any provocations addressed to the interlocutors that can cause a negative response. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.12. Abbreviations and allusions to common obscene and offensive language, such as "HZ", "PNH", etc. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.13. Motives of a nationalist or racist nature, as well as messages that discriminate against someone on the basis of age, gender, religion or social status. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.14. Quoting someone else\'s  message (including personal) containing words and expressions that are not allowed by the forum rules, without prior editing. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.15. Jokes about newcomers and other characters in the League that may be misunderstood. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.16. Persistently imposing your negative opinion on moderators, administrators or the League as a whole. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.17. Advertising a player, team or tournament in all topics and sections, except for the appropriate ones (Transfer / Rent / Registration and teams ...). Exceptions: It is allowed to post about players / teams in the national forums of the federation to which the player / team belongs. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.18. Over-quoting. This makes the message difficult to read and unnecessarily loads the topic. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.19. Any materials (and links to them) of a pornographic or erotic nature, scenes of violence, discussion of a political orientation; messages that violate a person\'s  right to privacy, as well as the publication of messages that are otherwise contrary to the laws and norms of morality. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.4.20. Spam (mass writing of any kind of advertisement or other type of messages) is prohibited. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.5. You should take into account the specifics of such a form of communication as a forum. In the forum, all messages are stored indefinitely. Therefore, in the forum it is customary to create messages that are not of momentary interest (especially only for individual participants), but messages that will be interesting to read to all visitors and some time after they are written. Personal correspondence in a general topic is considered offtopic. For personal correspondence there are private messages. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.6. It is forbidden to discuss the store and its users in a negative way, the sale / purchase of teams and players for real money. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.7. Personal showdowns and provocations on the forum are prohibited. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.8. It is forbidden to post links and references to other online rugby projects, as well as advertise other services and sites that are not related to the League, without the prior permission of the Administration (including in the signature). It is also forbidden to publish links to unlicensed commercial software (warez), programs for cracking it (cracks) and key generators, as well as to materials protected by copyright (books, music, videos, etc.). </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.9. Messages in any language other than Russian (using the Russian alphabet) are prohibited. Users of the Russian-language forum should understand what other participants are writing. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.10. Unauthorized moderation is prohibited. Those. when a member of the forum, who is not a moderator of this forum, makes comments to other members. Use the "complaint" button. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 2.11. Users are prohibited from accepting the right to communicate on behalf of any (especially a banned or lost access to the forum) user. </p>
