<p class = "strong text-justify" id = "3"> 3. Punishments. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 3.1. A warning is issued in the event that the offender did not greatly violate the rules and at the same time might not have known about it (unintentionally). For three active warnings, the offender receives a minor fine. The warning is valid for 30 days. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 3.2. A small fine is issued for an intentional or rather serious violation, as well as for repeated violation of the same paragraph of the Rules. A small penalty puts the user into read-only mode. The minor penalty is valid for 3 days. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 3.3. A large fine is issued for a fairly serious deliberate violation, as well as for repeated violation of the same paragraph of the Rules and contempt for the actions of moderators. A large penalty, like a small one, puts the user in read-only mode. A large fine is valid for a week. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 3.4. Disqualification is issued for a very serious willful violation, for demonstrative hooliganism on the forum. Disqualification denies the user access to the forum for a week. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 3.5. The received punishments may, by decision, be accompanied by a monetary fine to the manager who commits deliberate and / or repeated violations of the forum rules and cannot be corrected. In case of particularly persistent opposition to the moderators, we have the right to ban the user on the forum or refuse to provide services to the violator on the site. </p>
<p class = "text-right text-size-3"> [<a href="#0"> to content </a>] </p>
<p class = "strong text-justify" id = "4"> 4. Complaints to the moderator. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 4.1. Any active visitor to the forum can help the moderators by reporting violations of the rules of using the forum through complaints to the moderator. Moderators will be notified of your complaint and are required to respond to it. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 4.2. Authors of complaints should familiarize themselves with the opinion of the moderators about the message they left. It is forbidden to enter into disputes with moderators about the reaction to the complaint. You can send your possible disagreement with the actions of a particular moderator to technical support. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 4.3. Repeated writing of unfounded complaints is prohibited. Thus, you distract moderators from the really important work. In case of violation of this rule, moderators can punish the author of the complaint. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 4.4. Active and successful assistance to moderators through the system of writing complaints and assistance to newcomers on the forum is encouraged if an experienced manager wants to join the team of site and forum moderators. </p>
<p class = "text-right text-size-3"> [<a href="#0"> to content </a>] </p>
<p class = "strong text-justify" id = "5"> 5. Complaints about the actions of the moderators. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 5.1. Any visitor to the forum can appeal against the punishment imposed on him personally by the moderators in a special topic on the forum "Complaints against the actions of moderators". In this thread, he will receive a response from the moderator. It is forbidden to enter into disputes with moderators after the final response of the moderators to the complaint. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 5.2. You can send your possible disagreement with the actions of a particular moderator to technical support. </p>
<p class = "text-justify"> 5.3. Repeated writing of unfounded complaints is prohibited. Thus, you distract moderators from the really important work. In case of violation of this rule, moderators can punish the author of the complaint. </p>
